[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the need for efficient allocation of counter-terrorism resources, geographically and in terms of the potential for officers trained in counter-terrorism to be deployed where necessary to other policing activities; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the importance of police officers involved in public-facing counter-terrorism work (whether a house raid or a port stop) understanding the implications of their actions for the communities most affected. 
